Context:
The text provides information about an informational session being offered at George Brown College. The session aims to help students navigate the college environment and connect with peers and student ambassadors. Topics to be covered include an overview of George Brown's academic centres and schools, academic teams and service areas, course outlines, and success strategies.

The event registration is requested to be done in advance. Interested individuals can sign up on the website to receive updates about application deadlines, college news, events, tours, and more. Contact information for the college is provided, including a phone number (416-415-2000) and TTY number (1-877-515-5559), as well as an email address (ask.george@georgebrown.ca). The college's social media hub is also mentioned.

The text includes a disclaimer stating that the information on the website is subject to change without notice and should not be considered as a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are advised to verify George Brown College fee requirements.
